<h3> Brief </h3> 

<p>

I am a Microsoft Endowed Professor
in <a href="http://www.cs.washington.edu">Computer Science and
Engineering</a> at the <a href="http://www.washington.edu">University
of Washington</a>.  I teach databases and do research in data
management, where I apply formal theory to novel and difficult data
management tasks.  I worked on semistructured data, probabilistic
databases, parallel query evaluation on a cluster, causal reasoning in
databases, information theory for cardinality estimation, recursive
querie.  For a short bio please see <a href="bio.html">here</a>.

</p>

<p>

My <a href="https://files.oakland.edu/users/grossman/enp/Erdos1.html">Erdos</a> number
is 2.

</p>

